The paper deals with algorithms for evolutionary trees, which are rooted trees with labeled leaves representing species. This falls under the category of computational biology, which is often classified under cs.DS (data structures) or cs.CG (computational geometry). The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which could place it under cs.LG (machine learning) or cs.DM (discrete mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses optimization and complexity analysis, which could place it under cs.GT (computational complexity).
